org.epics.util.text

Class CsvParserResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.epics.util.text.CsvParserResult

  • public class CsvParserResult
extends Object
    The result of the CSV parsing.

    This class contains all the information about the parsing: whether it was successful, an error message, the parsed data, the parsed header and the column type.

    TODO: the error handling could be extended to include multiple error messages while still giving a best effort result (e.g. skipping the lines that can't be parsed).

    Author:
    carcassi

      • getColumnValues

        public List<Object> getColumnValues()
        The data of each column.

        Depending on the type, the data will be stored in a List (for Objects) and in a ListNumber (for primitive data). For example, if the column type is String, then one can expect a List<String>. If it's double, then one can expect a ListDouble.

        Returns:
        the list of column data
